The word śrī could be considered a  second auspicious opening formula (see translations in 

                 and in 

                ), but it appears to be an honorific prefix to the issuing placename as in vijaya-śrī-palakkaḍa-sthānāt (INSPallava00007) and śrīmad-vijaya-daśanapurādhiṣṭhānāt (INSPallava00247).
